			<h4>Typical User Behavior</h4>
			<p>
				Inbound and outbound calling and messaging are some of the core features that RingCentral customers frequently use on the mobile app. As much as the team wanted to enable these same two-way features on a watch, we had to prioritize only activities that would generate brief, meaningful, and simple interactions that would also be supported by the device’s limited technology.
			</p>
			<p>
				In designing this app, we understood that users interacting with a watch would primarily consume more content than they would create. For RingCentral’s real-time communication product, consumption activities referred to answering, reading, and responding to incoming calls and messages, which would occur more frequently than creating new calls and messages.
			</p>
			<img class="col-centered" src="/images/projects/iwatch-project/creation-vs-consumption.png">

			<h4>User Goal</h4>
			<p>
				The user goal was to accomplish all the primary consumption activities feasible from a mobile phone on a watch:
			</p>
